sect1.simpara:
The Stock Arrives screen must be used to add the stock to the database. Before adding stock of a drug, it is important to add the drug itself using the Add a New Drug screen, if this has not already been done. For more information on this, see Adding Drugs. It is also important that the distribution clinic for which the stock is intended has been added. For more information on this, see Adding Distribution Clinics. To add stock, log into the system and select
Stock & Dispensing
from the main screen. A new screen, the Stock Control Screen, will appear. From this screen, select Stock Arrives . The Stock Arrives at Pharmacy screen will appear. It looks like this:

Fill in at least the doctor's name and surname (the compulsory fields, marked with
). The other fields are recommended, but not required. When you are finished, click *Save
to add the doctor. To clear all the text fields, press Clear . To leave the screen without saving the doctor, press Cancel .

Fill in at least the doctor's name and surname (the compulsory fields, marked with
). The other fields are recommended, but not required. When you are finished, click *Save
to save your changes to the doctor. To clear all the text fields, press Clear . To leave the screen without saving the doctor, press Cancel .

To perform a deletion, select
Stock & Dispensing
from the main screen. Then, select Stock,Prescription And Package Deletions. You should see the following screen:

To access the Destroy Stock screen, select
Stock & Dispensing
from the main screen. Then, select Destroy Stock . You should see the screen below:
